description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a self-motivated and hardworking individual to join the Clinical Education Team based at Wexham and Heatherwood hospital. We are looking for a passionate and experienced individual to take on the role of Learning Environment Lead for Bands 2-4. You will be part of the Clinical Education team whose aim is to support and facilitate learning for all staff at Frimley Health NHS trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is responsible for coordinating the clinical learning for bands 2-4. The post holder will be responsible for the coordination of the care assistant induction programme and care certificate. The post holder will coordinate and facilitate the nursing associate and associate practitioner training programmes; they will be the primary link between the Trust, HEE and AEIs, to facilitate the clinical education of pre-registration nursing associates and associate practitioners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder must have the ability to work as part of a team as well as being able to work autonomously. The role requires an ability to act as an expert resource, provider and leader in documentation within clinical areas with a flexible and adaptable approach, responding to the clinical demands within the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Laura Clarke&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Matron for Clinical Education&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address laura.clarke29@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 07770653469&lt;/p&gt;
